featured_reviews.review_id:
My recent visit to McDonald's left me a bit disappointed. As a fan of their classic apple pies, I was looking forward to enjoying one with my meal. Unfortunately, to my dismay, they were out of apple pies during my visit. It was quite disappointing as it's a signature item that I always look forward to when visiting McDonald's.

The absence of the apple pie made me reconsider my order, and I ended up getting a refund, which didn't quite hit the spot. I understand that inventory issues can happen, but it's disappointing when a staple item like the apple pie is unavailable.

On the positive side, the rest of the meal was as expected from McDonald's - tasty and satisfying. The service was relatively quick, and the staff was friendly. However, the lack of apple pies did put a damper on the overall experience.

I hope McDonald's takes note of this issue and ensures a more consistent supply of their signature items in the future to avoid similar letdowns for other customers.

featured_reviews.review_id: The place is dirty.  Flies are buzzing around everywhere and the food just doesn't taste the same as a regular outlet.  The last time I was there, I saw a bunch of flies buzzing around and thought that 'This is what's likely over all over the food' and I walked out without buying anything.  The staff never smiles and barely acknowledges your presence.  Maybe that's a cultural thing based on the fact that they all seem to be from the same area of the world.  It is a fairly busy place, however, and I'm sure their clientele isn't always nice...which may have some affect on their attitude.  Who knows?  It's just not a positive experience.

featured_reviews.review_id: If there were 0 stars, that's what they get. We walk in for my husband's coffee and muffin. No one at the cash but a lady ( who was the manager) just looked at us and talked to coworkers and ignored us at the till.....then she realized she was working so she approached us, no smile, no apology..just non verbal rudeness. Took our order, we got the muffin. Husband went back to the counter because there was no knife. Then his butter packet was warmed up with the muffin...you can see the foil at the edges burnt up....he had to go back and tell her, no apology. Ruined our afternoon. Tables are dirty, workers have that zoned-out don't-care look. If the manager displayed bad customer relations, what do we expect from the crew? NEVER  going back. I hope every worker is replaced by robots/machines. Maybe we'll get an apology or better service.
